Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report
==========================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the portfolio project.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Fetched Latest Documentation
Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart).

### 2. Framework Identification
Identified this as a Next.js project using the App Router based on:
- Presence of `app/layout.tsx` (App Router structure)
- Next.js version 16.2.6 in package.json
- Package manager: npm (package-lock.json present)

### 3. Package Installation
Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm:
```bash
npm install @vercel/analytics
```

### 4. Code Changes

**Modified: portfolio/app/layout.tsx**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag of the root layout
- Followed the official Next.js App Router pattern from documentation
- Preserved all existing code structure, metadata, fonts, and styling

### 5. Verification Steps Completed
✓ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✓ TypeScript compilation passed
✓ All pages generated without errors
✓ Linter ran successfully (pre-existing warnings unrelated to Analytics)
✓ Lock file updated properly

### 6. Files Modified
- `portfolio/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `portfolio/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `portfolio/package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree

## Next Steps
To complete the setup:
1. Deploy to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

## Implementation Notes
- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body tag as recommended
- No breaking changes were made to existing code
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router
- All dependencies installed successfully without conflicts
